## 10. Rollback Plan

In case of data issues or critical bugs:
1. **Fallback to Default Store**: If a record has no `storeId`, the system resolves it to a default central store ID rather than throwing an exception.
2. **Revert Rules**: Maintain a copy of the previous permissive `firestore.rules` file to quickly restore global reads/writes if users report access issues.
3. **Database Restoration**: Since all migration operations use writes to new composite keys (`{storeId}_{sku}`), original global records (using `sku` keys) will be kept intact during the double-write phase to ensure zero loss of historical data.
